Object.Field: CSTM IKM MSSQL Incremental Update (SQLDW - CTAS)

COMPONENT NAME: IKM MSSQL Incremental Update
AUTHOR: Oracle, TGarrod
Description : - Integration Knowledge Module - Integrates data in an Microsoft Azure SQLDW or PDW target table in incremental update mode. - Inexistent rows are inserted; already existing rows are updated. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled. - When using this module with a journalized source table, it is possible to synchronize deletions. - Uses CTAS to create the FLOW table
Restrictions: - Comparison of data is made using the Update Key defined in the interface. It has to be set. - If UPDATE=true at least one target column, which is not part of the update key, must have a mapping expression assigned - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore. - Deletes are commited regardless of the COMMIT option - If CREATE_STATS_ON_FLOW = true the KM will Create stats on the UPDATE KEY Columns - IF UPDATE_STATS_ON_TARGET=true then KM will update stats on the target table (this is important for TRUNCATE and LOAD as PWD and SQLDW do not manage stats like a normal SQL DB).
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Identifies and updates rows of the Target Datastore depending on the value of the UPDATE_KEY columns of the target datastore records.
Commit all data inserted or updated in the target datastore.
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected by flow control in a previous execution of this interface.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
This option enables/disables index creation on flow table.
HEAP, CLUSTERED COLUMNSTORE INDEX, CLUSTERED INDEX
Create Flow table I$ using CTAS

DECLARE @distributionType varchar(25) DECLARE @distributionColumn varchar(500) = '' DECLARE @sql varchar(8000) DECLARE @JOINCOLUMN varchar(500) = '<%=odiRef.getColList("","[COL_NAME]|", "", "", "UK") %>' DECLARE @distributionClause varchar(500) DECLARE @object_id INT = OBJECT_ID('<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("SCHEMA")%>.<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("RES_NAME")%>') DECLARE @loop INT = (SELECT MAX(d.column_id) FROM sys.pdw_column_distribution_properties d INNER JOIN sys.columns c ON c.object_id = d.object_id WHERE d.distribution_ordinal = 1 AND c.column_id = d.column_id AND d.object_id = @object_id ) DECLARE @column_id INT = (SELECT MIN(d.column_id) FROM sys.pdw_column_distribution_properties d INNER JOIN sys.columns c ON c.object_id = d.object_id WHERE d.distribution_ordinal = 1 AND c.column_id = d.column_id AND d.object_id = @object_id )
SET @distributionType= (SELECT DISTINCT distribution_policy_desc FROM sys.pdw_table_distribution_properties WHERE object_id = @object_id )
--Begin Loop to get list of HASH distributiong types WHILE (@column_id<=@loop AND @distributionType= 'HASH') BEGIN
SET @distributionColumn = @distributionColumn + (SELECT c.name + '|' FROM sys.pdw_column_distribution_properties d INNER JOIN sys.columns c ON c.object_id = d.object_id WHERE d.distribution_ordinal = 1 AND c.column_id = d.column_id AND d.object_id = @object_id AND c.column_id = @column_id ) SET @column_id = (SELECT MIN(d.column_id) FROM sys.pdw_column_distribution_properties d INNER JOIN sys.columns c ON c.object_id = d.object_id WHERE d.distribution_ordinal = 1 AND c.column_id = d.column_id AND d.object_id = @object_id AND c.column_id< @column_id)
END
SET @distributionClause = CASE WHEN @distributionType= 'HASH' AND @distributionColumn=@JOINCOLUMN ---Join is being done on the distribution column - so lets forcible distribute on that THEN 'HASH(<%=odiRef.getColList("","[COL_NAME]", ",", "", "UK")%>)' ELSE 'ROUND_ROBIN' --Default to ROUND_ROBIN as data movement will be needed anyway!! END
SET @sql = ' create table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "((INS or UPD) and !TRG) ")%>, IND_UPDATE ) WITH ( DISTRIBUTION= ' + @distributionClause + ', <% if (odiRef.getOption("TABLE_TYPE").equals("CLUSTERED INDEX") ) { %><%=odiRef.getOption("TABLE_TYPE")%>(<%=odiRef.getColList("","[COL_NAME]", ",", "", "UK") %>)<%} else {%><%=odiRef.getOption("TABLE_TYPE")%><%};%>
)
AS
<%for (int i=odiRef.getDataSetMin(); i <= odiRef.getDataSetMax(); i++){%> <%=odiRef.getDataSet(i, "Operator")%> select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(i,"", "CAST([EXPRESSION] as [DEST_CRE_DT])", ",\n\t", "", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%>, <% if (odiRef.getDataSet(i, "HAS_JRN").equals("1")) { %> JRN_FLAG IND_UPDATE <%} else {%> ''I'' IND_UPDATE <%}%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom(i)%> where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJoin(i)%> <%=odiRef.getFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy(i)%> <%=odiRef.getHaving(i)%> <%}%>'
